# ── Runtime data — never commit ────────────────────────────────────────────
# The skipper's logbook is real data, not fixtures. The working database lives
# at ~/logbook/ and backups at ~/OneDrive/logbook/ — both OUTSIDE this repo —
# so these globs are the real guard against a stray copy being committed.
# (NB: intentionally NO bare `logbook/` rule — that would match and ignore the
#  source package of the same name. See docs/logbook-scope.md §3.6.)
*.db
*.db-journal
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
*.csv
backups/

# ── Local configuration — template committed, live file not ────────────────
# config.json carries machine-specific paths and the engine-hours baseline.
config.json

# ── Python ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.venv/
venv/
.pytest_cache/
.coverage
htmlcov/

# ── Editors / OS / tooling ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
.DS_Store
.claude/settings.local.json
